vlanVoiceAgingTimeout.name: vlanVoiceAgingTimeout
vlanVoiceAgingTimeout.description: The vlanVoiceAgingTimeout indicates the time (in units of minutes) from when the last OUI MAC was ageout from the FDB the port will be removed from the Voice VLAN. The default value for vlanVoiceAgingTimeout object is 1440 minutes (24 hours). The value of this object must be restored from non-volatile storage after a re-initialization of the management system.

vlanVoiceTable.name: vlanVoiceTable
vlanVoiceTable.description: A table containing static configuration information for each voice VLAN configured into the device and dynamic port membership. All entries are permanent and will be restored after the device is reset.

vlanVoiceEntry.name: vlanVoiceEntry
vlanVoiceEntry.description: Information for a voice VLAN configured into the device by management.

vlanVoicePriority.name: vlanVoicePriority
vlanVoicePriority.description: An administratively assigned Priority, which will be used for all traffic on the voice vlan, this gives the packets the requested priority (CoS) within the bridge.

vlanVoicePriorityRemark.name: vlanVoicePriorityRemark
vlanVoicePriorityRemark.description: Remark VPT on tagged frames egress the voice vlan according. to priority true.false

vlanVoiceRowStatus.name: vlanVoiceRowStatus
vlanVoiceRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

vlanVoiceOUITable.name: vlanVoiceOUITable
vlanVoiceOUITable.description: A table containing static global configuration information for Voice VLANs OUI MAC Prefixes. All entries are permanent and will be restored after the device is reset.

vlanVoiceOUIEntry.name: vlanVoiceOUIEntry
vlanVoiceOUIEntry.description: Information for a voice VLANs OUI MAC Prefixes configured into the device by management.

vlanVoiceOUIPrefix.name: vlanVoiceOUIPrefix
vlanVoiceOUIPrefix.description: The index value used to identify the OUI MAC Prefix component associated with this entry. The value of this object is used as an index to the vlanVoiceOUITable. Voice VLANs OUI Prefix is the first 3 most significant octets of the MAC address.

vlanVoiceOUIDescription.name: vlanVoiceOUIDescription
vlanVoiceOUIDescription.description: An optional text that describes the OUI.

vlanVoiceOUIEntryRowStatus.name: vlanVoiceOUIEntryRowStatus
vlanVoiceOUIEntryRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

vlanVoicePortTable.name: vlanVoicePortTable
vlanVoicePortTable.description: A table containing static and dynamic per port configuration information for Voice VLAN. All entries are permanent and will be restored after the device is reset.

vlanVoicePortEntry.name: vlanVoicePortEntry
vlanVoicePortEntry.description: Static and dynamic per port information for a voice VLAN.

vlanVoicePortEnable.name: vlanVoicePortEnable
vlanVoicePortEnable.description: Enable this port to be a candidate to be added into the Voice VLAN.

vlanVoicePortVlanIndex.name: vlanVoicePortVlanIndex
vlanVoicePortVlanIndex.description: The Voice VLAN-ID the port is a candidate to be in.

vlanVoicePortSecure.name: vlanVoicePortSecure
vlanVoicePortSecure.description: Specify this port to be in Secure Mode when entering the Voice VLAN. In Secure mode only frames with MAC prefix matched to one of the OUI table prefixes are accepted, otherwise dropped.

vlanVoicePortCurrentMembership.name: vlanVoicePortCurrentMembership
vlanVoicePortCurrentMembership.description: Port's current status of membership in Voice VLAN. Port's possible values of membership in Voice VLAN: 'Active(1)' - Port is currently added to a Voice VLAN . 'NotActive(2)' - Specifies either that port is a candidate to be in Voice VLAN or disabled.

vlanVoicePortQosMode.name: vlanVoicePortQosMode
vlanVoicePortQosMode.description: Port's current QOS mode in Voice VLAN. Possible values: 'src(1)' - Only traffic with OUI prefix in the source MAC received QOS of the Voice Vlan. 'all(2)' - All traffic through that port received QOS of the Voice Vlan.

vlanVoiceOUISetToDefault.name: vlanVoiceOUISetToDefault
vlanVoiceOUISetToDefault.description: The vlanVoiceOUISetToDefault indicates that vlanVoiceOUITable should be set to it's default values if existed (OUI default prefixes). To do so the vlanVoiceOUITable should be previuosly deleted by usual entries destroying. This object behaviors as write-only than reading this object will always return 'false'.

vlanPrivateEntry.description: Private vlan entry which contains the private vlan definition.

vlanPrivateVid.name: vlanPrivateVid
vlanPrivateVid.description: The static vlan ID which is set to one of the private vlan types.

vlanPrivateType.name: vlanPrivateType
vlanPrivateType.description: private vlan types: primary - Carries traffic from promiscuous ports. promiscuous port can communicate with all ports of the same PVLAN, including the isolated and community ports of the same PVLAN. isolated - Carries traffic from isolated ports. isolated ports can communicate only with the promiscuous ports of the same PVLAN. community - Carries traffic from community ports. community ports of the same community can communicate among themselves and with the promiscuous ports of the same PVLAN.

vlanPrivatePrimaryVid.name: vlanPrivatePrimaryVid
vlanPrivatePrimaryVid.description: The primary vlan ID which has defined in VlanPrivateEntry and which is associated with secondary vlan (in vlanPrivateMapTable). vlanPrivatePrimaryVid is equivalent to vlanPrivateVid when vlanPrivateVid is primary vlan.

vlanPrivateStatus.name: vlanPrivateStatus
vlanPrivateStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.

vlanPrivateMapPrimaryVid.name: vlanPrivateMapPrimaryVid
vlanPrivateMapPrimaryVid.description: The primary private vlan ID which is associated with the secondary (isolated or community) vlan (vlanPrivateMapSecondaryVid).

vlanPrivateMapSecondaryVid.name: vlanPrivateMapSecondaryVid
vlanPrivateMapSecondaryVid.description: The secondary private vlan ID which is associated with the primary vlan (vlanPrivateMapPrimaryVid).

vlanPrivateMapPrimaryPorts.name: vlanPrivateMapPrimaryPorts
vlanPrivateMapPrimaryPorts.description: The private vlan promiscuous ports mode which are belongs to the association of vlanPrivateMapPrimaryVid and vlanPrivateMapSecondaryVid.

vlanPrivateMapSecondaryPorts.name: vlanPrivateMapSecondaryPorts
